   - Summary of key terms (informative, not a substitute for the full license):
     - You must provide attribution to the original authors and this repository for reused code.
     - Non-commercial use only.
     - ShareAlike: derivative works must be licensed under the same CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

2) Documentation (README and other original textual content authored by Warren Samuelson Jayakumar)
   - License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
     <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/>
   - You are free to share and adapt the documentation for any purpose, even commercially, provided you give appropriate credit.

3) Figures/Images from third parties

- Figures reproduced from the SLAM3R paper or other third-party sources are NOT covered by the above licenses. They are © their respective rights holders and are used here for scholarly/research purposes with attribution. See THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md for details. If you are a rights holder and believe any material should be removed or updated, please open an issue or contact the maintainer.

Notes

- Where any conflict appears between this overview and the full license texts referenced above, the full license texts govern.
- This repository does not grant any trademark rights.
- For commercial licensing inquiries regarding code, contact the original rights holders of the upstream work.
